        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 18 at 2:33PM EST by NWS Indianapolis IN</headline>
        <description>At 233 PM EST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northwest of Hutsonville, or 12 miles north of Robinson, moving
east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Jasonville, Shelburn, Farmersburg, Hymera, Fairbanks, Coalmont, and
Graysville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
